        "created_at": "2025-11-08T22:34:05.841Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I propose a concept of ‚Äúviews‚Äù for every conversation.</p>\n<p>The default view shows every message in the conversation - this is how all chats look now</p>\n<p>Another view could show every message in that conversation from a particular sender or list of senders or category of senders (such as group admins), or excluding a particular sender or list/category of senders</p>\n<p>Another view could show every message that is a reply to a certain message, or a reply to any message, or excludes replies to any message</p>\n<p>Another view could show every message containing a text string, or without it</p>\n<p>If the currently displayed filtered view is different from the default view, there should always be some kind of UI indicator that lets you know, and allows you to switch to the default view, but is also unobtrusive enough to be easily ignored</p>\n<p>The list of chats should be able to show multiple views of the same chat, configured by the user.</p>\n<p>Replying to a message will automatically give you the option to create a new view for only replies to that message, while also filtering those replies from the previous view. This would implement threading for those who want it.</p>\n<p>Views could have separate notification preferences which override those of the default view.</p>\n<p>Views would be ordered, so that rules for higher-order views take precedence over lower ones. By default this would be oldest to newest, but the user could rearrange them</p>\n<p>Groups could offer predefined views, such as for important announcements</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
